<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The fulvous dorsal body and the aedeagus with a broad and parallel-sided apical process, distinguish this species from 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. divisa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="divisa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. divisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Originally from Vietnam, we confirm that 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. kimotoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kimotoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. kimotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in China.
</paragraph>
